Hello
I am 30 years old
I started coke at 20 years old,
I never took it every day, wasn't super addicted.
I used to have 1 or 2 at most once or twice a month, but for about 6 months, maybe a year, I've been unable to control myself when I drink alcohol.
Even though before I used to promise not to go looking for a sniff, after 2 or 3 drinks I start getting hot and I tell myself "come on, we only have one life, let's go" and it's impossible to control myself, too much urge to get some.
So here's the thing, I know that the problem is alcohol at the base, but it's crazy impossible to quit among family and friends for the aperitif, etc.
Is someone having this problem?
Thank you
stop drinking and the problem will be solved
it sometimes takes self-discipline to stop...
didn't you at least talk about it to your family doctor?
seeing an addict could do you good, especially for "evaluating" your consumption
Actually, it's in the evening that it's harder to maintain mentally.
the day it's okay
Hello,
I am polysubstance-dependent with a big alcoholism issue,
I have been sober from alcohol for a few years, but I can't convince myself that I won't drink a drop of alcohol when I want to, maybe not enough willpower.
I do sometimes binge drink on occasion because it's stronger than me and as soon as I start, I can't stop.
after I sleep very badly and am sick the next day and especially I hate myself,
I am ashamed of who I become when I drink, and I suffer from it,
I can't drink normally
I drink all my glasses bottom up,
why do I have this relationship with alcohol while so many people can drink normally??
I have not drunk anything for 10 days,
this weekend I am invited to a birthday and I am very very afraid,
if you've lived the same thing or have passed the threshold, I'll take everything that can help.
thank you for reading and i await your responses.
friendly
