I want to say that before this bad trip, I was shooting 20 shells a day and would do some big hits every two months with heavy tripping (Taz, coke, LSD, and all the rest)... For three years,
now I am going to tell you how it is going.
a Good week awaits me
We had planned with 3 colleagues to take 10g of speed, 1g of MDMA, and 2 bottles of LSD.
every Friday evening everything goes well
we have to consume 5gr of speed plus all the md,
Saturday morning after a sleepless night, I go to work just in the morning from 9h to 12h in the afternoon,
on has not continued,
I keep going on my own tapping shells and taking speed.
at the end of the afternoon, evening arrives and 2 other colleagues join us and we had decided to take LSD on the beach (Personally, I wasn't reassured),
a colleague held the glass for me with a drop from the lsd bottle
I hesitated at first, then after I told myself come on I'll take it (something I shouldn't have).
the evening continued normally and the two so-called colleagues had decided to really get on our nerves....
on that famous beach there were people and one of the two colleagues told us "there's someone looking for trouble, let's fight it out...."
I tell myself the product needs to go down because I can't fight like that
so I forced myself to resist the product,
the, the paranoia starts to overwhelm me all in making a mise-en-scène
the two other colleagues who hadn't taken anything starts to look for the guys who want to harm us
I being totally wired told myself it's going to happen at any moment,
time passes nothing happens.
brief we leave the beach and then we go to my place,
I ask them if the guys are following us,
he does not respond,
we arrive at my place and there he leaves us all in the lurch, alone at my place with my girlfriend who was sleeping...
I continue my bad all night
can't sleep, I'm thinking and at the slightest noise I grab a bat and go out...
the day rises and I start to fall asleep because I just became aware that there was nothing,
the night passes normally,
I get up and I am still under the effect of LSD and the rest.
I tell myself it's normal
so it was Sunday and the next day I had to work.
the day is passing normally
I tap some shells then I nap,
Sunday passes and Monday arrives
I still feel like I'm being painted over,
I still say these normal things with the box that I have taken....
so at 2pm I had to take the job
I eat a little and I take a big dose of speed so I can feel good at work...
so I take the car and then I go to work
getting to work, as soon as I open the store, I start feeling dizzy, my heart starts beating at 200, and I feel like I'm going to have a fainting spell,
to reassure myself, I'm going to buy some Snickers bars and something to drink,
after that I go back to work and another crisis...
panicked I called my mom... because my colleagues weren't there....
after my mother brings me to the doctor
he asks me what I did and there I spill all my secrets
and my mom took me in the end; she knows I was suspicious...
The Doctor tells me to wait for the product to come down, it will take a few months, and that's all,
I told him I had vision problems
I told him I had vision problems
He told me that it was normal too and that it would go down soon,
for my anxiety attacks, he prescribed me lizanxia, an antilithic drug, finally against anxiety,
I take 1 in the morning 1 in the evening,
It calms me down but the voices in my head don't stop,
it often gives me a good headache...
after this Bad I've stopped using no more shells nothing,
My girlfriend doesn't understand what's happening to me and doesn't really care.
I fired him,
My colleagues also don't care either, so I also fired him/her.
at the same time I moved ,
I am currently living with my mother, but I have found an apartment.
but I cannot live there because I have anxiety attacks.
In addition to that, I have a bunch of thoughts in my head
recently had suicidal thoughts... voices that make me feel guilty or provoke anxiety crises.
Currently, it's been 5 months since I did this bad, and in terms of my vision, I still have to look behind a mirror.
finally these troubles especially when it's sunny...
the voices in my head don't stop from morning until night...
my thoughts blend through force of always thinking alike
I feel like I'm living the same day over and over.
with all of that, I no longer recognize myself,
I always have my job, I don't have any friends left apart from 2 cousins and my brother who are far from me,
I work alone also
and so the whole day I am alone except in the evening when my mother is here...
I will consult an ophthalmologist at the beginning of January, but I don't think it will improve much.
in fact I don't know what to do anymore except wait and maybe get out...
Thank you for reading my message and sorry for the spelling errors.
if someone has already lived through this experience, can they give me some advice. Thanks
Hello to you Cllaude271. To start, I do not take LSD.
I sometimes take speed or empty shells but not LSD, ketamine, or anything else.
I think you should simply see another doctor or a toxicologist (I don't know if that's the exact term)
If after 5 months you're still experiencing this kind of "side effect," that's really bad.
So without wanting to panic you, you should see a toxicologist who I think will prescribe you treatment or emergency antidotes.
Otherwise, there are free numbers or specialized forums. Good continuation. Peace
Hello Claude271,
To have gone through the state you describe multiple times (due to mixtures of chatter, micropoints, taz, keta, in fact, everything that passed through there),
if I can give you a piece of advice, it's simply to tell you that all of this is just psychological.
In general, the more you stress about these states, the worse they will become.
A very simple thing in these cases, you take deep breaths, you breathe slowly, and you settle in a place where you feel safe, and not too close to the walls (yes, sometimes you can have the feeling that they are closing in on you).
After several months following a use, especially when you mix substances, you can experience effects, especially after a sudden cessation of the substances.
Don't worry, it's just a matter of time.
But as Claude532 said, consulting a psychiatrist can also help you get rid of these voices that clutter your head.
Keep the catch, and stay positive.
Thank you both for your responses
I will try to be patient,
